# 1. Executive Summary

The application was vulnerable to **Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI)** within the `blog-post-author-display` parameter.

The application used the **Tornado** template engine to dynamically render the author's display name above blog comments. By injecting malicious template syntax into this parameter, it was possible to escape the original template context, execute arbitrary Python code on the server, and ultimately execute operating system commands.

Successful exploitation resulted in arbitrary command execution and deletion of the target file:

```
/home/carlos/morale.txt
```

