# 10. Impact Analysis

A successful attacker can execute arbitrary Python code on the server.

Potential consequences include:

- Remote Code Execution (RCE)
- Reading sensitive files
- Modifying application data
- Executing operating system commands
- Privilege escalation
- Deploying malware
- Complete server compromise

This vulnerability represents one of the highest-impact classes of web application vulnerabilities.

---

# 11. Root Cause

The application renders user-controlled data directly inside Tornado template expressions.

No validation or escaping is performed before rendering, allowing attackers to inject arbitrary template syntax.

The template engine executes injected Python code with the privileges of the web application.

---

# 12. Recommendations

## Critical

Never render user-controlled input directly inside server-side templates.

## Critical

Use automatic escaping and strict context separation provided by the template engine.

## High

Validate user input using allowlists instead of blocklists.

## High

Disable access to dangerous Python modules whenever possible.

## Medium

Run the application using a low-privileged operating system account.

## Medium

Implement server-side monitoring for template syntax such as:

```
{{
}}
{%
%}
```

