# 14. Conclusion

The assessment confirmed the presence of a **Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI)** vulnerability within the Tornado template engine.

By escaping the original template context, arbitrary template expressions were successfully evaluated. This allowed execution of arbitrary Python code through the `os` module and resulted in operating system command execution.

The vulnerability ultimately enabled deletion of the target file, demonstrating that an attacker could fully compromise the underlying server if additional security controls were not in place.

Because SSTI frequently leads to Remote Code Execution, it should be considered a **Critical** vulnerability and remediated immediately.
